{\n "nbformat": 4,\n "nbformat_minor": 5,\n "metadata": {\n  "kernelspec": {"display_name": "Python 3", "language": "python", "name": "python3"},\n  "language_info": {"name": "python", "version": "3.10.0"}\n },\n "cells": [\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-title",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "# Phase 2 — Preprocessing Pipeline\n",\n    "## XAI-Based Network Intrusion Detection System\n",\n    "\n",\n    "**Dataset:** CICIDS-2017  \n",\n    "**Author:** Chandra Sekhar Chakraborty  \n",\n    "**Prerequisite:** Run `01_eda.ipynb` first — this notebook reads `data/processed/eda_meta.json`\n",\n    "\n",\n    "---\n",\n    "\n",\n    "### Preprocessing Roadmap\n",\n    "1. [Setup & Load EDA Metadata](#1-setup--load-eda-metadata)\n",\n    "2. [Load Raw Dataset](#2-load-raw-dataset)\n",\n    "3. [Step 1 — Clean: Remove Inf & NaN](#3-step-1--clean-remove-inf--nan)\n",\n    "4. [Step 2 — Drop Zero-Variance & Constant Features](#4-step-2--drop-zero-variance--constant-features)\n",\n    "5. [Step 3 — Encode Labels](#5-step-3--encode-labels)\n",\n    "6. [Step 4 — Train / Test Split (Stratified 80/20)](#6-step-4--train--test-split-stratified-8020)\n",\n    "7. [Step 5 — MinMax Feature Scaling](#7-step-5--minmax-feature-scaling)\n",\n    "8. [Step 6 — SMOTE on Training Set Only](#8-step-6--smote-on-training-set-only)\n",\n    "9. [Step 7 — Save Processed Datasets & Artifacts](#9-step-7--save-processed-datasets--artifacts)\n",\n    "10. [Preprocessing Summary & Phase 3 Handoff](#10-preprocessing-summary--phase-3-handoff)"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s1",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": ["## 1. Setup & Load EDA Metadata"]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-imports",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "import os\n",\n    "import glob\n",\n    "import json\n",\n    "import warnings\n",\n    "import time\n",\n    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "import numpy as np\n",\n    "import pandas as pd\n",\n    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",\n    "import matplotlib.ticker as mticker\n",\n    "import seaborn as sns\n",\n    "import joblib\n",\n    "\n",\n    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",\n    "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler, LabelEncoder\n",\n    "from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── Reproducibility ──────────────────────────────────────\n",\n    "RANDOM_SEED = 42\n",\n    "np.random.seed(RANDOM_SEED)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── Paths ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",\n    "DATA_RAW_DIR  = '../data/raw/'\n",\n    "DATA_PROC_DIR = '../data/processed/'\n",\n    "MODELS_DIR    = '../models/'\n",\n    "os.makedirs(DATA_PROC_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n",\n    "os.makedirs(MODELS_DIR,    exist_ok=True)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── Display ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n",\n    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n",\n    "pd.set_option('display.float_format', lambda x: f'{x:.4f}')\n",\n    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",\n    "    'figure.facecolor': '#1a1a2e', 'axes.facecolor': '#16213e',\n",\n    "    'axes.edgecolor': '#0f3460',   'axes.labelcolor': '#e0e0e0',\n",\n    "    'xtick.color': '#e0e0e0',      'ytick.color': '#e0e0e0',\n",\n    "    'text.color': '#e0e0e0',       'grid.color': '#0f3460',\n",\n    "    'font.family': 'monospace',    'figure.dpi': 120\n",\n    "})\n",\n    "ATTACK_COLORS = [\n",\n    "    '#00d4ff','#ff6b6b','#ffd93d','#6bcb77','#4d96ff',\n",\n    "    '#ff9f43','#a29bfe','#fd79a8','#55efc4','#fdcb6e',\n",\n    "    '#e17055','#74b9ff','#00cec9','#b2bec3','#dfe6e9'\n",\n    "]\n",\n    "print('✅ Libraries loaded')\n",\n    "print(f'   scikit-learn  : {__import__(\"sklearn\").__version__}')\n",\n    "print(f'   imbalanced-learn: {__import__(\"imblearn\").__version__}')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-load-meta",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "META_PATH = os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'eda_meta.json')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "if not os.path.exists(META_PATH):\n",\n    "    raise FileNotFoundError(\n",\n    "        f'eda_meta.json not found at {META_PATH}.\\n'\n",\n    "        'Please run notebooks/01_eda.ipynb first to generate it.'\n",\n    "    )\n",\n    "\n",\n    "with open(META_PATH, 'r') as f:\n",\n    "    meta = json.load(f)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "LABEL_COL      = meta['label_col']\n",\n    "FEATURE_COLS   = meta['feature_cols']\n",\n    "NUMERIC_COLS   = meta['numeric_cols']\n",\n    "CLASS_NAMES    = meta['class_names']\n",\n    "N_CLASSES      = meta['n_classes']\n",\n    "ZERO_VAR_COLS  = meta['zero_variance_cols']\n",\n    "INF_COLS       = meta['inf_cols']\n",\n    "NULL_COLS      = meta['null_cols']\n",\n    "TOP20_FEATURES = meta['top_20_features']\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print('✅ EDA metadata loaded from eda_meta.json')\n",\n    "print(f'   Label column    : \"{LABEL_COL}\"')\n",\n    "print(f'   Total features  : {len(FEATURE_COLS)}')\n",\n    "print(f'   Numeric features: {len(NUMERIC_COLS)}')\n",\n    "print(f'   Classes         : {N_CLASSES}')\n",\n    "print(f'   Zero-var cols   : {len(ZERO_VAR_COLS)}')\n",\n    "print(f'   Inf cols        : {len(INF_COLS)}')\n",\n    "print(f'   Null cols       : {len(NULL_COLS)}')\n",\n    "print()\n",\n    "print('  Class names:')\n",\n    "for cls in CLASS_NAMES:\n",\n    "    cnt = meta['class_counts'].get(cls, 0)\n",\n    "    print(f'    {cls:45s}: {cnt:>8,}')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s2",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 2. Load Raw Dataset\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> We reload the full raw CICIDS-2017 data. Set `SAMPLE_MODE = True` for a quick test run (100K rows per file).\n",\n    "> The preprocessing here is **deterministic** — same input always produces the same output."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-load-data",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "SAMPLE_MODE = False   # Set True for fast iteration (loads 100K rows per CSV)\n",\n    "SAMPLE_ROWS = 100_000\n",\n    "\n",\n    "csv_files = sorted(glob.glob(os.path.join(DATA_RAW_DIR, '*.csv')))\n",\n    "if not csv_files:\n",\n    "    raise FileNotFoundError(\n",\n    "        f'No CSV files in {DATA_RAW_DIR}.\\n'\n",\n    "        'Download CICIDS-2017 from https://www.unb.ca/cic/datasets/ids-2017.html'\n",\n    "    )\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print(f'📂 Loading {len(csv_files)} CSV file(s) — SAMPLE_MODE={SAMPLE_MODE}')\n",\n    "t0 = time.time()\n",\n    "dfs = []\n",\n    "for f in csv_files:\n",\n    "    _df = pd.read_csv(f, low_memory=False, nrows=SAMPLE_ROWS if SAMPLE_MODE else None)\n",\n    "    _df.columns = _df.columns.str.strip()\n",\n    "    dfs.append(_df)\n",\n    "    print(f'   {os.path.basename(f):50s} → {len(_df):>8,} rows')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "df = pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)\n",\n    "elapsed = time.time() - t0\n",\n    "print(f'\\n✅ Combined: {df.shape[0]:,} rows × {df.shape[1]} cols  ({elapsed:.1f}s)')\n",\n    "print(f'   Memory  : {df.memory_usage(deep=True).sum() / (1024**2):.1f} MB')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s3",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 3. Step 1 — Clean: Remove Inf & NaN\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> **Strategy (from EDA findings):**\n",\n    "> - Replace `+Inf` and `-Inf` with `NaN` first\n",\n    "> - Fill `NaN` in each column with the column's **median** (robust to outliers)\n",\n    "> - Any remaining NaN rows are dropped\n",\n    "> - This approach is preferred over filling with 0 (which introduces a fake \\\"zero flow\\\" signal) or max (which inflates outliers)"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-clean",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "df_clean = df.copy()\n",\n    "rows_before = len(df_clean)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 1. Strip label column whitespace ─────────────────────\n",\n    "df_clean[LABEL_COL] = df_clean[LABEL_COL].str.strip()\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 2. Select only numeric feature columns + label ───────\n",\n    "all_numeric = df_clean.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\n",\n    "df_clean = df_clean[all_numeric + [LABEL_COL]].copy()\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 3. Replace +Inf / -Inf with NaN ──────────────────────\n",\n    "inf_mask = np.isinf(df_clean[all_numeric])\n",\n    "n_inf_total = inf_mask.sum().sum()\n",\n    "df_clean[all_numeric] = df_clean[all_numeric].replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 4. Fill NaN with column median (fit on whole set) ────\n",\n    "medians = df_clean[all_numeric].median()\n",\n    "df_clean[all_numeric] = df_clean[all_numeric].fillna(medians)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 5. Drop any remaining NaN rows ───────────────────────\n",\n    "n_nan_rows = df_clean.isnull().any(axis=1).sum()\n",\n    "df_clean = df_clean.dropna()\n",\n    "rows_after = len(df_clean)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print('STEP 1 — CLEANING REPORT')\n",\n    "print('─' * 50)\n",\n    "print(f'  Rows before  : {rows_before:>10,}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Inf values   : {n_inf_total:>10,}  → replaced with NaN, then median-filled')\n",\n    "print(f'  Remaining NaN rows dropped : {n_nan_rows:>5,}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Rows after   : {rows_after:>10,}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Rows removed : {rows_before - rows_after:>10,}  ({(rows_before-rows_after)/rows_before*100:.3f}%)')\n",\n    "print()\n",\n    "# Verify no remaining NaN or Inf\n",\n    "assert df_clean[all_numeric].isnull().sum().sum() == 0, '❌ NaN still present!'\n",\n    "assert not np.isinf(df_clean[all_numeric].values).any(),  '❌ Inf still present!'\n",\n    "print('  ✅ No NaN remaining')\n",\n    "print('  ✅ No Inf remaining')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s4",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 4. Step 2 — Drop Zero-Variance & Constant Features\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> Features with zero variance carry no information — they are identical for every sample.\n",\n    "> Keeping them wastes computation and can mislead certain models. We drop them here."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-drop-zerovar",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "feature_cols_numeric = [c for c in all_numeric if c != LABEL_COL]\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Compute std on cleaned data (no Inf/NaN)\n",\n    "stds = df_clean[feature_cols_numeric].std()\n",\n    "zero_var_cols = stds[stds == 0].index.tolist()\n",\n    "near_zero_var_cols = stds[stds < 1e-8].index.tolist()  # catch floating-point near-zero\n",\n    "\n",\n    "cols_to_drop = list(set(zero_var_cols + near_zero_var_cols + ZERO_VAR_COLS))\n",\n    "cols_to_drop = [c for c in cols_to_drop if c in df_clean.columns]  # safety filter\n",\n    "\n",\n    "if cols_to_drop:\n",\n    "    df_clean = df_clean.drop(columns=cols_to_drop)\n",\n    "    print(f'STEP 2 — DROPPED {len(cols_to_drop)} ZERO-VARIANCE FEATURE(S):')\n",\n    "    for c in cols_to_drop:\n",\n    "        print(f'  - {c}')\n",\n    "else:\n",\n    "    print('STEP 2 — No zero-variance features found. Nothing dropped.')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Update feature list\n",\n    "FEATURE_COLS_FINAL = [c for c in df_clean.columns if c != LABEL_COL]\n",\n    "print(f'\\n  ✅ Final feature count: {len(FEATURE_COLS_FINAL)}')\n",\n    "print(f'  (down from {len(feature_cols_numeric)} before zero-var removal)')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s5",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 5. Step 3 — Encode Labels\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> Scikit-learn models need integer class labels. We use `LabelEncoder` to map each\n",\n    "> attack class name to a unique integer. We save the encoder so predictions can be\n",\n    "> decoded back to human-readable names in the dashboard."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-encode-labels",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "le = LabelEncoder()\n",\n    "df_clean['label_encoded'] = le.fit_transform(df_clean[LABEL_COL])\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Build mapping for reference\n",\n    "label_map = dict(zip(le.classes_, le.transform(le.classes_)))\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print('STEP 3 — LABEL ENCODING')\n",\n    "print('─' * 55)\n",\n    "print(f'  {\"Class Name\":45s}  {\"Encoded ID\":<5}  {\"Sample Count\"}')\n",\n    "print('  ' + '─' * 65)\n",\n    "for cls_name, cls_id in sorted(label_map.items(), key=lambda x: x[1]):\n",\n    "    cnt = (df_clean['label_encoded'] == cls_id).sum()\n",\n    "    print(f'  {cls_name:45s}  {cls_id:<5}  {cnt:>10,}')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Save encoder\n",\n    "encoder_path = os.path.join(MODELS_DIR, 'label_encoder.pkl')\n",\n    "joblib.dump(le, encoder_path)\n",\n    "print(f'\\n  ✅ LabelEncoder saved → {encoder_path}')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Save label map as JSON for the dashboard\n",\n    "with open(os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'label_map.json'), 'w') as f:\n",\n    "    json.dump(label_map, f, indent=2)\n",\n    "print(f'  ✅ label_map.json saved → {DATA_PROC_DIR}')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s6",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 6. Step 4 — Train / Test Split (Stratified 80/20)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> **Why stratified?** CICIDS-2017 is severely imbalanced. Without stratification, rare classes\n",\n    "> like Infiltration (36 samples) could end up entirely in training or entirely in test.\n",\n    "> Stratified split preserves the class ratio in both splits.\n",\n    ">\n",\n    "> **Important:** SMOTE is applied to the training set ONLY — the test set must reflect\n",\n    "> real-world class distribution to give honest evaluation metrics."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-split",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "X = df_clean[FEATURE_COLS_FINAL].values\n",\n    "y = df_clean['label_encoded'].values\n",\n    "\n",\n    "TEST_SIZE = 0.20\n",\n    "\n",\n    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",\n    "    X, y,\n",\n    "    test_size=TEST_SIZE,\n",\n    "    stratify=y,\n",\n    "    random_state=RANDOM_SEED\n",\n    ")\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print('STEP 4 — TRAIN / TEST SPLIT')\n",\n    "print('─' * 55)\n",\n    "print(f'  Strategy   : Stratified (preserves class ratios)')\n",\n    "print(f'  Test size  : {TEST_SIZE*100:.0f}%')\n",\n    "print(f'  Train rows : {X_train.shape[0]:>10,}  (features: {X_train.shape[1]})')\n",\n    "print(f'  Test rows  : {X_test.shape[0]:>10,}  (features: {X_test.shape[1]})')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Verify class balance maintained\n",\n    "print('\\n  Class distribution in train vs test:')\n",\n    "print(f'  {\"Class\":45s}  {\"Train\":>9}  {\"Test\":>8}')\n",\n    "print('  ' + '─' * 68)\n",\n    "for cls_id, cls_name in enumerate(le.classes_):\n",\n    "    n_train = (y_train == cls_id).sum()\n",\n    "    n_test  = (y_test  == cls_id).sum()\n",\n    "    print(f'  {cls_name:45s}  {n_train:>9,}  {n_test:>8,}')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s7",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 7. Step 5 — MinMax Feature Scaling\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> **Why MinMaxScaler?** Network flow features span wildly different ranges:\n",\n    "> - `Destination Port` ranges 0–65535\n",\n    "> - `Flow Duration` ranges 0–120,000,000 (microseconds)\n",\n    "> - `Fwd Packet Length Mean` ranges 0–1500\n",\n    ">\n",\n    "> MinMaxScaler maps all features to [0, 1], preventing large-range features from dominating\n",\n    "> distance-based calculations. LSTM especially benefits from normalized input.\n",\n    ">\n",\n    "> **Critical rule:** Fit on train set ONLY — transform both train and test.\n",\n    "> Fitting on test data would cause **data leakage**."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-scale",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(0, 1))\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Fit ONLY on training data, then transform both splits\n",\n    "t0 = time.time()\n",\n    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",\n    "X_test_scaled  = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",\n    "elapsed = time.time() - t0\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Verify bounds\n",\n    "train_min = X_train_scaled.min()\n",\n    "train_max = X_train_scaled.max()\n",\n    "test_min  = X_test_scaled.min()\n",\n    "test_max  = X_test_scaled.max()\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print('STEP 5 — MINMAX SCALING')\n",\n    "print('─' * 50)\n",\n    "print(f'  Fit on     : training set ONLY ({X_train.shape[0]:,} rows)  [no data leakage]')\n",\n    "print(f'  Time taken : {elapsed:.2f}s')\n",\n    "print(f'  Train range: [{train_min:.6f}, {train_max:.6f}]  ← should be [0, 1]')\n",\n    "print(f'  Test range : [{test_min:.6f}, {test_max:.6f}]  ← may slightly exceed [0,1] (OK)')\n",\n    "print()\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Spot-check a few features\n",\n    "print('  Feature scaling spot-check (original → scaled):')\n",\n    "sample_features = FEATURE_COLS_FINAL[:5]\n",\n    "for i, feat in enumerate(sample_features):\n",\n    "    orig_min = X_train[:, i].min()\n",\n    "    orig_max = X_train[:, i].max()\n",\n    "    sc_min   = X_train_scaled[:, i].min()\n",\n    "    sc_max   = X_train_scaled[:, i].max()\n",\n    "    print(f'  {feat[:38]:38s}: [{orig_min:.2f}, {orig_max:.2f}] → [{sc_min:.4f}, {sc_max:.4f}]')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Save scaler\n",\n    "scaler_path = os.path.join(MODELS_DIR, 'minmax_scaler.pkl')\n",\n    "joblib.dump(scaler, scaler_path)\n",\n    "print(f'\\n  ✅ MinMaxScaler saved → {scaler_path}')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s8",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 8. Step 6 — SMOTE on Training Set Only\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> **Why SMOTE?** The CICIDS-2017 dataset has extreme class imbalance:\n",\n    "> - BENIGN: ~2.27 million samples\n",\n    "> - Infiltration: ~36 samples (imbalance ratio ~63,000:1)\n",\n    ">\n",\n    "> Without balancing, models learn to predict BENIGN for everything and still achieve 80%+ accuracy.\n",\n    "> SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Over-sampling Technique) generates **synthetic samples** for minority\n",\n    "> classes by interpolating between existing minority samples — not duplicating them.\n",\n    ">\n",\n    "> **Applied to training set ONLY.** The test set is never touched — it reflects real distributions.\n",\n    ">\n",\n    "> **k_neighbors note:** For very rare classes (< 6 samples in training), SMOTE uses\n",\n    "> `k_neighbors = n_samples - 1` automatically to avoid errors."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-smote",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "from collections import Counter\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── Count samples per class before SMOTE ─────────────────\n",\n    "counts_before = Counter(y_train)\n",\n    "min_class_count = min(counts_before.values())\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# k_neighbors must be < min class samples\n",\n    "k_neighbors = max(1, min(5, min_class_count - 1))\n",\n    "print(f'STEP 6 — SMOTE')\n",\n    "print(f'─' * 55)\n",\n    "print(f'  Rarest class has {min_class_count} training samples → k_neighbors={k_neighbors}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Running SMOTE... (this may take several minutes on the full dataset)')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "t0 = time.time()\n",\n    "smote = SMOTE(\n",\n    "    sampling_strategy='not majority',  # oversample all minority classes\n",\n    "    k_neighbors=k_neighbors,\n",\n    "    random_state=RANDOM_SEED,\n",\n    "    n_jobs=-1\n",\n    ")\n",\n    "X_train_bal, y_train_bal = smote.fit_resample(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",\n    "elapsed = time.time() - t0\n",\n    "\n",\n    "counts_after = Counter(y_train_bal)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print(f'  Done in {elapsed:.1f}s')\n",\n    "print(f'\\n  Shape before SMOTE : {X_train_scaled.shape}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Shape after  SMOTE : {X_train_bal.shape}')\n",\n    "print(f'\\n  {\"Class\":45s}  {\"Before\":>9}  {\"After\":>9}  {\"Added\":>9}')\n",\n    "print('  ' + '─' * 80)\n",\n    "for cls_id, cls_name in enumerate(le.classes_):\n",\n    "    before = counts_before.get(cls_id, 0)\n",\n    "    after  = counts_after.get(cls_id, 0)\n",\n    "    added  = after - before\n",\n    "    marker = '  ← SMOTE' if added > 0 else ''\n",\n    "    print(f'  {cls_name:45s}  {before:>9,}  {after:>9,}  {added:>9,}{marker}')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-smote-plot",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "# ── Visualize class balance before vs after SMOTE ────────\n",\n    "class_labels = le.classes_\n",\n    "before_counts = [counts_before.get(i, 0) for i in range(N_CLASSES)]\n",\n    "after_counts  = [counts_after.get(i, 0)  for i in range(N_CLASSES)]\n",\n    "\n",\n    "x = np.arange(N_CLASSES)\n",\n    "width = 0.38\n",\n    "\n",\n    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 6))\n",\n    "fig.suptitle('Class Distribution — Before vs After SMOTE (Training Set)',\n",\n    "             fontsize=13, fontweight='bold', color='#00d4ff')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "for ax, scale, title_suffix in zip(\n",\n    "    axes, ['linear', 'log'], ['Linear Scale', 'Log Scale (reveals minority classes)']):\n",\n    "    bars1 = ax.bar(x - width/2, before_counts, width, label='Before SMOTE',\n",\n    "                   color='#4d96ff', alpha=0.85, edgecolor='none')\n",\n    "    bars2 = ax.bar(x + width/2, after_counts,  width, label='After SMOTE',\n",\n    "                   color='#6bcb77', alpha=0.85, edgecolor='none')\n",\n    "    if scale == 'log':\n",\n    "        ax.set_yscale('log')\n",\n    "    ax.set_xticks(x)\n",\n    "    ax.set_xticklabels([c[:18] for c in class_labels], rotation=45, ha='right', fontsize=7)\n",\n    "    ax.set_ylabel('Sample Count', fontsize=9)\n",\n    "    ax.set_title(title_suffix, fontsize=10, color='#e0e0e0')\n",\n    "    ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",\n    "    ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda v, _: f'{int(v):,}'))\n",\n    "\n",\n    "plt.tight_layout()\n",\n    "os.makedirs('../docs/eda_plots', exist_ok=True)\n",\n    "plt.savefig('../docs/eda_plots/06_smote_class_balance.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",\n    "plt.show()\n",\n    "print('💾 Saved → ../docs/eda_plots/06_smote_class_balance.png')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s9",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 9. Step 7 — Save Processed Datasets & Artifacts\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> We save four items:\n",\n    "> 1. `train_balanced.csv` — SMOTE-balanced training set (scaled features + encoded labels)\n",\n    "> 2. `test.csv` — unmodified test set (scaled but NOT SMOTE'd)\n",\n    "> 3. `minmax_scaler.pkl` — fitted scaler (already saved in Step 5)\n",\n    "> 4. `label_encoder.pkl` — fitted encoder (already saved in Step 3)\n",\n    "> 5. `preprocessing_meta.json` — full record of all decisions made here\n",\n    ">\n",\n    "> Phase 3 notebooks load `train_balanced.csv` and `test.csv` directly — no re-processing needed."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-save",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "print('STEP 7 — SAVING PROCESSED DATA & ARTIFACTS')\n",\n    "print('─' * 55)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 1. Build DataFrames ───────────────────────────────────\n",\n    "df_train = pd.DataFrame(X_train_bal,  columns=FEATURE_COLS_FINAL)\n",\n    "df_train['label'] = y_train_bal\n",\n    "\n",\n    "df_test  = pd.DataFrame(X_test_scaled, columns=FEATURE_COLS_FINAL)\n",\n    "df_test['label']  = y_test\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 2. Save CSVs ──────────────────────────────────────────\n",\n    "train_path = os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'train_balanced.csv')\n",\n    "test_path  = os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'test.csv')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "t0 = time.time()\n",\n    "df_train.to_csv(train_path, index=False)\n",\n    "df_test.to_csv(test_path,   index=False)\n",\n    "elapsed = time.time() - t0\n",\n    "\n",\n    "train_size_mb = os.path.getsize(train_path) / (1024**2)\n",\n    "test_size_mb  = os.path.getsize(test_path)  / (1024**2)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print(f'  ✅ train_balanced.csv → {train_path}')\n",\n    "print(f'     Rows: {len(df_train):,}   Cols: {df_train.shape[1]}   Size: {train_size_mb:.1f} MB')\n",\n    "print(f'  ✅ test.csv           → {test_path}')\n",\n    "print(f'     Rows: {len(df_test):,}   Cols: {df_test.shape[1]}   Size: {test_size_mb:.1f} MB')\n",\n    "print(f'  Time: {elapsed:.1f}s')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 3. Save feature column list ──────────────────────────\n",\n    "with open(os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'feature_cols.json'), 'w') as f:\n",\n    "    json.dump(FEATURE_COLS_FINAL, f, indent=2)\n",\n    "print(f'  ✅ feature_cols.json  → {DATA_PROC_DIR}')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── 4. Save preprocessing metadata ───────────────────────\n",\n    "preprocessing_meta = {\n",\n    "    'n_features_original'  : len(FEATURE_COLS),\n",\n    "    'n_features_final'     : len(FEATURE_COLS_FINAL),\n",\n    "    'features_dropped'     : cols_to_drop,\n",\n    "    'feature_cols'         : FEATURE_COLS_FINAL,\n",\n    "    'label_col'            : 'label',\n",\n    "    'label_map'            : {str(v): k for k, v in label_map.items()},\n",\n    "    'n_classes'            : N_CLASSES,\n",\n    "    'test_size'            : TEST_SIZE,\n",\n    "    'smote_k_neighbors'    : k_neighbors,\n",\n    "    'smote_strategy'       : 'not majority',\n",\n    "    'scaler'               : 'MinMaxScaler [0,1]',\n",\n    "    'train_rows_before_smote': int(X_train_scaled.shape[0]),\n",\n    "    'train_rows_after_smote' : int(X_train_bal.shape[0]),\n",\n    "    'test_rows'              : int(X_test_scaled.shape[0]),\n",\n    "    'random_seed'            : RANDOM_SEED\n",\n    "}\n",\n    "\n",\n    "meta_out_path = os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'preprocessing_meta.json')\n",\n    "with open(meta_out_path, 'w') as f:\n",\n    "    json.dump(preprocessing_meta, f, indent=2)\n",\n    "print(f'  ✅ preprocessing_meta.json → {meta_out_path}')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-verify-save",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "# ── Verify artifacts on disk ──────────────────────────────\n",\n    "print('ARTIFACT VERIFICATION')\n",\n    "print('─' * 55)\n",\n    "artifacts = [\n",\n    "    os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'train_balanced.csv'),\n",\n    "    os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'test.csv'),\n",\n    "    os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'label_map.json'),\n",\n    "    os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'feature_cols.json'),\n",\n    "    os.path.join(DATA_PROC_DIR, 'preprocessing_meta.json'),\n",\n    "    os.path.join(MODELS_DIR, 'minmax_scaler.pkl'),\n",\n    "    os.path.join(MODELS_DIR, 'label_encoder.pkl'),\n",\n    "]\n",\n    "all_ok = True\n",\n    "for path in artifacts:\n",\n    "    exists = os.path.exists(path)\n",\n    "    size   = os.path.getsize(path) / (1024**2) if exists else 0\n",\n    "    status = '✅' if exists else '❌ MISSING'\n",\n    "    print(f'  {status}  {os.path.basename(path):35s}  {size:.2f} MB')\n",\n    "    if not exists:\n",\n    "        all_ok = False\n",\n    "print()\n",\n    "if all_ok:\n",\n    "    print('  ✅ All artifacts verified — Phase 2 complete!')\n",\n    "else:\n",\n    "    print('  ❌ Some artifacts missing — re-run cells above')"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-s10",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 10. Preprocessing Summary & Phase 3 Handoff\n",\n    "\n",\n    "> Full audit trail of every decision made in this notebook."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-summary",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "print('=' * 65)\n",\n    "print('PHASE 2 — PREPROCESSING COMPLETE')\n",\n    "print('=' * 65)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print(f'''\n",\n    "DECISIONS MADE:\n",\n    "  1. Inf values        → replaced with NaN, then median-filled\n",\n    "  2. NaN rows          → dropped after median fill\n",\n    "  3. Zero-variance     → {len(cols_to_drop)} columns dropped\n",\n    "  4. Label encoding    → LabelEncoder (integer IDs 0–{N_CLASSES-1})\n",\n    "  5. Train/test split  → 80/20 stratified (seed={RANDOM_SEED})\n",\n    "  6. Feature scaling   → MinMaxScaler [0,1] — fit on train only\n",\n    "  7. SMOTE             → 'not majority' strategy, k={k_neighbors}\n",\n    "\n",\n    "DATASET STATS:\n",\n    "''')\n",\n    "print(f'  Features (final)     : {len(FEATURE_COLS_FINAL)}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Train rows (raw)     : {X_train_scaled.shape[0]:,}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Train rows (+ SMOTE) : {X_train_bal.shape[0]:,}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Test rows            : {X_test_scaled.shape[0]:,}')\n",\n    "print(f'  Classes              : {N_CLASSES}')\n",\n    "print(f'''\n",\n    "ARTIFACTS SAVED:\n",\n    "  data/processed/train_balanced.csv    ← Phase 3 training input\n",\n    "  data/processed/test.csv              ← Phase 3 evaluation input\n",\n    "  data/processed/feature_cols.json     ← feature order for inference\n",\n    "  data/processed/label_map.json        ← decode predictions to names\n",\n    "  data/processed/preprocessing_meta.json\n",\n    "  models/minmax_scaler.pkl             ← apply to live inference input\n",\n    "  models/label_encoder.pkl             ← decode model output\n",\n    "\n",\n    "NEXT: notebooks/03_model_training.ipynb\n",\n    "  → Train Random Forest, XGBoost, LSTM\n",\n    "  → Evaluate DR, FAR, F1, ROC AUC\n",\n    "  → Save trained model artifacts\n",\n    "''')\n",\n    "print('=' * 65)"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-scaling-dist-plot",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "# ── Bonus: visualize feature value distribution before/after scaling ──\n",\n    "TOP5 = FEATURE_COLS_FINAL[:5]\n",\n    "idx  = [FEATURE_COLS_FINAL.index(f) for f in TOP5]\n",\n    "\n",\n    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 5, figsize=(20, 7))\n",\n    "fig.suptitle('Feature Distributions — Before vs After MinMaxScaling (Train Set, Top 5 Features)',\n",\n    "             fontsize=12, fontweight='bold', color='#00d4ff')\n",\n    "\n",\n    "for col_i, (feat, fi) in enumerate(zip(TOP5, idx)):\n",\n    "    raw_data    = X_train[:, fi]\n",\n    "    scaled_data = X_train_scaled[:, fi]\n",\n    "    clip_raw    = np.percentile(raw_data, 99)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    ax_raw = axes[0, col_i]\n",\n    "    ax_raw.hist(np.clip(raw_data, None, clip_raw), bins=50,\n",\n    "                color='#ff6b6b', edgecolor='none', alpha=0.85)\n",\n    "    ax_raw.set_title(feat[:22], fontsize=8, color='#e0e0e0')\n",\n    "    ax_raw.set_xlabel('Raw value', fontsize=7)\n",\n    "    if col_i == 0: ax_raw.set_ylabel('Before Scaling', fontsize=8)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    ax_sc = axes[1, col_i]\n",\n    "    ax_sc.hist(scaled_data, bins=50, color='#6bcb77', edgecolor='none', alpha=0.85)\n",\n    "    ax_sc.set_xlabel('Scaled value [0,1]', fontsize=7)\n",\n    "    if col_i == 0: ax_sc.set_ylabel('After Scaling', fontsize=8)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "plt.tight_layout()\n",\n    "plt.savefig('../docs/eda_plots/07_scaling_distributions.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",\n    "plt.show()\n",\n    "print('💾 Saved → ../docs/eda_plots/07_scaling_distributions.png')"\n   ]\n  }\n ]\n}